Acquisition:
   - Pugilist: level 1
Description:
   Primary Motion is the first thing taught in Pugilist training: a single,
   clean, efficient strike. Economy of Motion holds that no movement should
   be wasted — every action deliberate, every step purposeful. Primary Motion
   is not powerful. It is correct. The pyramid-construction labor tradition
   that produces Pugilists does not celebrate force; it celebrates precision
   of application. This is where that application begins.

   Damage is calculated from pseudo-level and Constitution (pug_attack
   helper, same as palmstrike, pummel). As the Pugilist advances, Primary
   Motion gives way to more specialized techniques from the Interior Forms
   curriculum.

   Syntax: primary motion <target>
   Requires POS_FIGHTING. Can be practiced to improve hit rate.
*******************************************************************************
